More than 400 women entrepreneurs will benefit from funding from a clean energy lobby.
 Energy 4 Impact has partnered with M-Changa, Africa’s leading crowdfunding platform, to increase access to funding for women clean energy micro-entrepreneurs in rural Kenya and Tanzania.
 The lobby said in a statement yesterday it would fund as many as 450 women entrepreneurs engaged in clean cooking and off-grid lighting supply chains in a bid to increase uptake of clean energy. 





